# Managed by nix (cfg/users/programs/claude/gitignore) — do not edit ~/.claude/.gitignore by hand; edit the cfg source and rebuild.
#
# Delivered by users/programs/claude/default.nix as a REAL file (copied on
# activation, NOT symlinked: git refuses to read a symlinked .gitignore — it
# opens with O_NOFOLLOW, so a symlinked one is silently ignored and everything
# gets staged). Edit here; it re-copies on the next rebuild.
#
# Allowlist: ignore everything, then re-include only specific config by exact
# pattern — never whole subtrees. A file that isn't listed stays untracked. This
# keeps sessions/, projects/, session-env/, caches, settings.local.json, and the
# nix-store symlinks (cfg-rules.md, skills/) out of the repo by default.
#
# Re-include is by extension, not `dir/**`, so an unrelated file dropped inside an
# allowlisted dir (e.g. memory/foo.bin) stays ignored.
*
!.gitignore
!CLAUDE.md
!memory/
!memory/*.md
!hooks/
!hooks/*.py
!rules/
!rules/*.md
